Class Processor

java.lang.Object
  apps.tree.scheduling.Processor

 class Processor
extends java.lang.Object

This class implements a processor that executes processes in the simulation system.

busy

boolean busy
Flag to indicate is processor is busy executing a process.

currProc

Process currProc
Process that is currently executing at this processor, if the processor is busy. After process gets its time slice, processor becomes idle, and the process can be retrieved, at which time this field is set to null.

getProcess

Process getProcess()
             throws BusyInterruptionException
Returns the process, if any, that finished its time time slice at this process, and has not been retrieved yet.

Returns:
Process, if any, that just finished its time slice of execution at this processor, null if no process.
Throws:
BusyInterruptionException - If this method is called when the processor is busy executing a process, i.e. the process' time slice is not yet done.
